=============================================================================
PART A - FOUNDATIONAL PLEADINGS
=============================================================================

1. PRELIMINARY SUBMISSIONS
1.1 This Statement of Claim is filed by the Claimant against the Respondent under the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 ("A&C Act"), seeking adjudication of contractual breaches, payment defaults, delay damages, and all consequential reliefs.
1.2 This pleading is structured to remain litigation-ready across the full lifecycle:
    (i) pre-award,
    (ii) post-award,
    (iii) Section 34 challenge stage,
    (iv) Section 36 stay/execution stage, and
    (v) High Court pendency.
1.3 The Claimant reserves the right to amend, supplement, or quantify claims upon production of withheld records, expert reports, and tribunal directions.

