=============================================================================
PART B - CAUSE OF ACTION AND BREACH THEORY
=============================================================================

6. BREACHES BY RESPONDENT
6.1 Failure to provide hindrance-free site and approvals.
6.2 Failure to certify and release RA bills in time.
6.3 Wrongful denial of variation / escalation.
6.4 Illegal levy or threat of LD/termination/blacklisting.
6.5 Any additional breach specific to case record.

7. LEGAL BASIS
7.1 Contract terms (GCC/SCC/technical specifications).
7.2 A&C Act, 1996 (Sections 16, 17, 18, 19, 23, 31, 34, 36).
7.3 Applicable infrastructure standards/contract doctrines:
    - CPWD / PWD specifications,
    - FIDIC principles (if contractually adopted),
    - IEEMA / escalation formulas,
    - MoRTH/IRC/IS codes (where applicable).
7.4 Principles of fairness, equal treatment, and reasoned decision-making in public contracts.

