=============================================================================
PART D - INTERIM RELIEF (SECTION 17)
=============================================================================

10. SECTION 17 INTERIM APPLICATION (WITHIN ARBITRATION)
10.1 Pending final adjudication, Claimant seeks:
    (i) restraint against coercive recoveries/encashment,
    (ii) direction to preserve records and digital trails,
    (iii) deposit/security for admitted dues,
    (iv) restraint against blacklist action based on disputed claims.
10.2 Balance of convenience lies in preserving status quo.
10.3 Irreparable injury would arise without interim protection.

=============================================================================
PART E - RESPONDENT COUNTER-CLAIM STRATEGY
=============================================================================

11. PRE-EMPTIVE RESPONSE TO COUNTER-CLAIMS
11.1 Any counter-claim for LD, risk-and-cost, incomplete work, or re-tender differential is denied unless strictly proved.
11.2 Respondent must prove:
    - lawful termination,
    - proper cure notices,
    - causal nexus,
    - quantified proof with primary records.
11.3 Set-off and adjustment objections reserved.

=============================================================================
PART F - POST-AWARD ENFORCEMENT, DECREE, STAY, HC PENDENCY
=============================================================================

12. AWARD TO BE TREATED AS DECREE (SECTION 36 FRAMEWORK)
12.1 Upon expiry/failure of Section 34 challenge (or subject to court orders), award is enforceable as a decree.
12.2 Claimant seeks liberty to execute before competent commercial/civil court having territorial and pecuniary jurisdiction.

13. SECTION 34 CHALLENGE AND STAY MANAGEMENT
13.1 Mere filing of Section 34 does not automatically stay enforcement.
13.2 If Respondent seeks stay under Section 36(2)/(3), Claimant seeks:
    (i) full deposit of awarded sum, or
    (ii) substantial security + strict timeline conditions.
13.3 Any stay must be conditional, reasoned, and proportionate.

14. HIGH COURT PENDENCY PROTOCOL
14.1 If challenge/appeal remains pending before High Court:
    (i) Claimant seeks expedited listing,
    (ii) periodic compliance affidavit on security condition,
    (iii) release of undisputed/secured portion subject to safeguards.
14.2 Claimant reserves right to seek vacation/modification of stay on breach of conditions.

15. EXECUTION / DECREE STEP-DOWN PLAN
15.1 Immediately post-award:
    - certified copy application,
    - computation memo,
    - demand notice for voluntary compliance.
15.2 On default:
    - execution filing with asset schedule,
    - garnishee/bank attachment prayer (as permissible),
    - disclosure of movable/immovable assets.
15.3 During HC pendency:
    - pursue conditional release and anti-delay directions.

